  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Ebola Treatment Unit Project (STEP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PCI is managing the US Department of Defense built Ebola Treatment Unit (ETU) in Ganta, Nimba County. PC will provide a controlled setting where medical care can be safely given to people infected with Ebola. PCI&#x2019;s role in managing the ETU will include both clinical and non-clinical components. It will include: (i) initial and on-going training of health facility staff in patient care and infection prevention and control (IPC); (ii) supportive monitoring and supervision of day to day operations and maintenance of the highest of standards of operation; (iii) Supply of Personal Protective Equipment (PPEs) in collaboration with the MOHSW/WHO; (iv) Support for the collection of data and reporting; (v) Administration of human resource functions and payment of salaries; (vi) Coordination of the activities of the ETU with other institutions and activities involved with the response including the MOHSW at the county and national levels, the National Case Management Committee, the ETU technical advisory sub-committee and WHO technical advisors stationed in Monrovia and Nimba County.  PCI will also promote the protection of individuals and families, including unaccompanied minors, at the ETU.  The Ganta ETU will be operated in close coordination with PCI&#x2019;s and other partners&#x2019; efforts in the region in community mobilization, the construction and management of Community Care Centers (CCC), contact tracing, and health system strengthening.</narrative>
  </description>
